text:
The food was amazing with many stalls and also a market at the back.

It was fast and efficent with friendly staff always there to help.

It was quite spacious even though the table may be a bit dirty.
Regularly I visit this hawker ctr. Many good food her.
Good and cheap garoupa steam boat $25, generals helping of garlic with tee wang mie $4 n sweet & sour rib (5pc of pork chop) rice $5.

*BEST CARROT CAKE IN SINGAPORE* from my personal point of view. It is not too soft or hard..is perfect. Chilli won't burn your lips even aunty puts a lots.. which I like( I love taste of spicy but not hot.).  Stall is located 01-19. Should give it a try!

The chicken cutlet fried rice is to die for. Will be back! The rice is very grainy and even though I dont like to eat mixed veg (small peas, carrots), the flavour of the rice is so aromatic that I happily finished all the veg!
